      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/36/58",
      "text": [
        " سَأَلَ اَلْمَرْزُبَانُ أَبَا اَلْحَسَنِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : عَنْ ذَبِيحَةِ وَلَدِ اَلزِّنَا وَ قَدْ عَرَفْنَاهُ بِذَلِكَ قَالَ \"لاَ بَأْسَ بِهِ وَ اَلْمَرْأَةُ وَ اَلصَّبِيُّ إِذَا اُضْطُرُّوا إِلَيْهِ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4178 - Safwan ibn Yahya narrated that Al-Marzuban asked Abu al-Hasan (as) about the slaughtered animal of a child born out of wedlock, and they were certain of his status.\nImam (as) said: \"There is no harm in it, and it is permissible for a woman and a child if they are in necessity.\""
        ]
      }
    },
